                    <WebAddress>http://www.ebrd.com/who-we-are/history-of-the-ebrd.html</WebAddress>
                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>History</Header>
                <Paragraph>In October of 1989, a month before German citizens dismantled parts of the Berlin Wall, President François Mitterrand of France proposed the establishment of a European bank to meet the challenges of emergent economic and political realities. In less than 2 years, the EBRD opened for business with its headquarters in London. To learn more about the role played by the EBRD in the transition from the end of the Cold War to a new European era, visit the "History of the EBRD" web page.</Paragraph>
